Blaenau, Ffestiniog, Merioneth, Wales}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid4927121\charrsid16072257 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid4927121 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Could you give your name and address please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 In full you mean? Hywel Berwyn Davies, 9 The Square, Blaenau Ffestiniog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you are married, when did you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 In 1926. Do you want the month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where were you born and when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 I was born on the second of March 1896 in Blaenau Ffestiniog. 72 High Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How many years did you live in the house in which you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well I lived there until 1912 when I went to the bank. That was for sixteen years. And then the family lived there for a long time afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did you go to the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh in Barmouth. And I lived in Brynt Air, Kings Crescent. And then I went down to live in Marine Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 In Barmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Then I went into the Army and after I came back in 1920 and after that I went to Hyddgrig where I got hold o
f the wife. And after that I - I went to Denbigh and then to Corwn and from Corwn to Trawsfynydd and from there to Llan Ffestiniog until I was sacked by them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Your family didn't move at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, they didn't. Only after my brother took over t
he shop. And then - two of my sisters and brother went to live in - went to live in Cromwell Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You had two sisters and a brother did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How many did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, in fact I was one of nine. Only the baby died at five days old.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was she the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. And Cadiog was the only one that didn't reach seventy, he was sixty-eight and a half when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What order did the brothers and sisters come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 A sister was the eldest, then a brother, another brother, then three sisters, and then me. And - then a smaller brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember how many years there were between the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well roughly about two years I'd say. But there are three and a half between my sister and me. The old people had second thoughts then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - twenty-nine I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh from Llan Drillog. Merionethshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What was his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh he was a carpenter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was that for his whole life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Yes, all the time he was a carpenter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he do any part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well apart from starting an orchestra in Blaenau, he started the first orchestra that ever was here, he was very keen on music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you ever remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well it was 1859. She was two years younger than my father which makes her twenty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did she come from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 From Coinwyd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she have a job before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Not to my knowledge she didn't. I never heard anything of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she work after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Not even a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No. Because my father was in a business, he kept a shop apart from being a - a carpenter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did he sell in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh - ironmongery and he made lots of cupboards - cabinets. Nothing like the cabinets they make - now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember how many rooms there were in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
There was the cellar, we ate in the cellar, and there were two back kitchens behind, one was a - a food room and the other was a cooking room. And then there was a coal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 shed and the shop took up two rooms that were in the house, then there was a bathroom and three bedrooms and an attic above that, where all the boys slept together in separate beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was there anyone else apart from your brothers and sisters and parents living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. Only the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, she had plenty of children. But sometimes a lady would come and help her with the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they do all the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother or father make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well my mother did most of it and my sisters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have new clothes or did you wear second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well they were - the clothes were mainly passed on from one to the other down the stairs of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you buy second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 hand clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, we didn't. We - we bought Sunday school suits and then the old Sunday suit became the everyday suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember where you bought the new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well there were plenty of drapers shops in Blaenau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was there a special time at which you bought new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I mean Blaenau was thriving in those days, Blaenau was at its best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about shoes, did you have new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 hand shoes? Or did you pass them on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No. we didn't. No, we always wore our shoes out and had new shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your father help your mother with the housework at all, with the cleaning or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, he didn't, there were plenty of children, there was no need.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 He didn't do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, he had enough work to do in the work shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he make the fire or decorate or repair the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - yes, I mean on a Sunday maybe he'd get up and make a fire, but as a rule my mother did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, I mean my father did that unless he got an outside builder in, if that was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When you were small did your father dress or undress you or give you a bath, read to you or tell you stories?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, my mother bathed us before we had a bath in a zinc tub in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your father read to you or tell you stories at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, he would read. Every Sunday night we'd be round the fire and he'd read a story from the Old Testament. And we'd reme
mber it then 'cos he'd read something interesting. So that we wouldn't forget it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he tell you stories at all, make them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 He didn't sort of tell his life story or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, very little. No, he said enough in the chapel. He was a Leader.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Very rarely because, as a rule, we just went out to play as children do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he look after you when your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh there was no purpose in him doing that because my older sisters looked after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have any regular tasks to carry out in the house to help your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Very little, maybe I'd polish the brasses on a Saturday, in order to get a ha'penny to spend, it was a ha'penny in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How long did you go on doing these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Until you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Yes. Or maybe 'til, I went - 'til I was over ten. When I started to become a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about your brothers and sisters, did they do tasks too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did the older children help the younger children at all with things they found difficult?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes - everyone pulled together, everyone helped each other. In everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about the younger children, did they have to do things for the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well they didn't have to, but often they would because it meant that they would benefit later on. Very often my sister used to take sandwiches up to my younger brother when he'd been sent to bed for being bad. He was sent to bed without supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they expect you to go to bed at a particular time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well, yes, we used to have to go at about eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Who put you in bed, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well my older sister did sometimes but I mean, as a rule, my brother and I went to bed by ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember when you first used to go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I should think we were children of about seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you share your bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 There were two beds - my two older brothers and my younger brother and I in another bed. And we used to sleep in the attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well there were two - bedrooms on the floor below the attic. My mother and father had one and my sisters
 had the other. And there were two in each bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Which room did you have a bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - when we had the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 inc tub we used to have a bath in the cellar in the - where the kitchen was. And then we had a - a very small bedroom converted into a bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh, it was during the first world war. 1914-'18.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How many times a week did you have to have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh once a week. On Saturday night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have clean clothes on Saturday too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh in the cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 That was the room where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Because it was half the size of the - of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 oor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no. No, very 
rarely. Even when we had visitors, I mean, preachers or something, they came to the cellar to eat. Because I mean the cooking room was attached to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of fire did your mother have to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh a coal fire. The old fashioned oven with a small boiler at the side to heat the hot water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - it must have been about eight o'clock. In order to get to school on time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were all members of the family present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, yes, they were. Unless my father had had his breakfast a little earlier to start work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother get up with your father if he did eat earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about the things you had to eat and drink, what were they usually for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well as it w
as a long time ago we usually had half an egg, 'cos it was such a large family which had to struggle in the beginning. Porridge was the first thing we had. And a boiled egg and sometimes bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have anything special on certain days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, nothing special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about dinner, when did you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh at twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were all the family present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did you usually have to eat or drink for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well meat and potatoes or stew and bread a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 nd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564  - and fried liver. Lots of different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have anything special on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, we'd have a leg of something - a joint, and always we'd have rice pudding. 'Cos Sundays - no, no, all the time. It was an easy thing to make for a crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - usually }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564  had that about seven o'clock, to get it out of the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was everyone there for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - no, off and on. Maybe my sisters were courting somewhere and then they didn't want supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did you usually have to eat or drink for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - very often we had milk and potato soup in the winter. We didn't have anything heavy except on a Saturday evening. We'd have haddock every Saturday night. That was special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother or father bake bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, my mother baked every week regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she bottle fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I don't remember her doing that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes, she made pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she make wine or medicine for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, she didn't
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she make beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. They were against that you see, that's why I started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother or father grow their own fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, 'cos we didn't have a garden. The workshop - carpenter's workshop was in the back. There wasn't really a garden, just a few }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 low}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
rs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 So she bought things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, she bought everything like that except for things we got from relatives, 'cos we had quite a few relatives who were farmers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about tinned or dried things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, I don't remember those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they keep any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well we had the odd dog or cat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How many times in a week did you have meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well nearly every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - very rarely. Not - not often at all. We'd have a tin of sardines or a tin of salmon here and there, specially if they'd saved a little money or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember having any extra through poaching at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well we had rabbit quite often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 But did your father poach at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, he didn't. No, no, we used to buy them. Because so many people came to the door and to the shop selling things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food in order that the family should have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. I don't. No, it was pretty even.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And your father didn't have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I didn't notice. But my brother and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 j}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 ust buried ourselves in the food, we didn't notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you allowed to talk during mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, everyone talked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat from what had been cooked or did you have to have what you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, we all ate the same. Whatever my mother gave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you had to eat it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Could you leave any behind on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, we couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 If there was something on the table like the salt that you wanted were you allowed to ask someone to pass it to you
 or wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well no, we just grabbed it really, there was salt on each side of the table. It was a pretty long table and so there'd be salt and pepper at one end and at the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you just took it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, we just helped ourselves. But very often people just passed it along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you allowed to ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, if you wanted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they expect you to hold your knife and fork in the right way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, we had to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about sitting in a correct way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, they didn't mind about that. No, there wasn't such a thing - oh well, we weren}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6766553\charrsid7017564 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 t to put our elbows on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, we couldn't, we had to keep - those to the side. I mean there wasn't any room for them in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you allowed to leave the table when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh we had to wait 'til everyone had finished, as a rule that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, and my father said grace, or one of us said grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have the same places each time at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember who served the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh my mother every time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was this done in any special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No, I mean my mother was - was the chief cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she dish it out to your father first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, as a rule my father got it first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember where your younger brother used to sit before he was old enough to feed himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I don't really have much memory of that, unless it was in a sort of baby chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother feed him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, or my sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You don't remember how old he was when he was allowed to join in with the family meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No I've no idea. I'm sure he sat down with us when he was three or four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 If you were worrying about something could you share this worry with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, I was able to tell her. The trouble was that if my brother and I had been bad boys somebody'd go over there and tell on us and my father would be there with the birch rod waiting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was your father easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he show affection to you too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. And he gave us a good beating if we swore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you share your worries with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How do you think your parents expected you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh we had to respect them like a mother or father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - yes, I mean if we did happen to quarrel the old man'd beat us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 He didn't like you fighting then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. But I mean we didn't quarrel very much as far as I can remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 If a child hit you were you allowed to hit him back, did your parents approve of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, they didn't. So I'd make sure I was outside when I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember what sort of people your parents hoped that you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well I think they hoped we'd grow up to be like them. And try to respect everybody, and be good children and go to chapel, that was the most important thing for my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What else did your parents think were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well I mean that really was the life, the chapel and everything, and music of course. And I mean, you know, my father - my mother had enough to do looking after eight-eight children - eight children that lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did they feel about swearing, you've already mentioned this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh my father got very angry when we swore. And I had a few slaps off him when I didn't realize he was nearby and I happened to swear, and my father would happen to be behind the door and he'd hit me unt
il I spun round. I'm afraid it was rather often. You know how children are amongst themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 If adults were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, she'd tell us to be quiet. We were only to speak when somebody spoke to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of punishments did you get if you did something that your parents disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh we had the birch rod. And with nothing on too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Your father did this did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, yes, my father. I mean my mother wouldn't have hit hard, the old man could hit hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How often do you think this happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well I'm afraid it happened more than once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother ever punish you like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. The punishment I got from my mother was to go to bed without supper. And to a chil
d that was a terrible punishment, that was when my sisters used to bring sandwiches up to me, they took pity on me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember a particular occasion on which you were punished, some particularly bad punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I mean they came so often. No one was special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember how you felt towards this form of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean I just took it as being part of life, that's how I took it. I mean I knew I'd done something out of place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Would you say that you received the ideas about how to behave from your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 There wasn't one that was more influential than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, there wasn't. Both of them were fairly similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were birthdays any different form other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well yes, there was a - a little difference, there was a special tea or something. Like a Sunday tea really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did you have, did you have pancakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, cakes that my mother had made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You - didn't have a party or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, there - there were too many in the family really for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have presents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, little things. Old fashioned presents, if you compare with the present day. It was just a little sixpenny toy in the old days. I mean in those days children thought more of a sixpenny present than they do of a six pound present now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember anything you did together with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well we used to have a party amongst the family and a few friends. We ha
d that every Christmas. But my younger sister, she used to compete in a - in the - in the hall here in the Eistedford at the - Independent - chapes Eistedford, and she did that at Christmas and so on Christmas evening she used to go to the Eistedford, and
 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 rest of us had a sort of party in the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have any musical instruments in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well there was an old violin but I have no memory of anyone playing it. And - but there was a piano and they all played that, except my o
lder sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well my younger sister. But my brother was with the Morowyn choir, the first one. He's the sole survivor. The first Morowyn choir that went to America.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Which one was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh Humphrey. He was a second tenor in the choir. He married - he did in September last year. He was eighty-seven and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you make music as a family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well there was a lot of singing, I mean we had a lot of singi
ng there on a Sunday night. Friends of my brothers and sisters would come round. But I mean I left the nest young. I was sixteen. But the bulk of them were a lot older than I was when they left home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, my father used to play a little. He'd play ball with us and hitting a balloon around at Christmastime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, plenty. All kinds of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well at that time my father was too bus
y during the day and we'd get the newspaper at seven o'clock at night. It was the Liverpool Echo - one ha'penny. That was what it cost in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember any magazines at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 My brother used to get Wild World and that came every we
ek - no, every month, and I've no memory except for Chapel magazines apart from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you say Wild World?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Wide World.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember seeing your mother and father read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well they didn't have much opportunity until we went to bed and then they read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember them reading aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well my father always read these stories from the Bible every Sunday night and - in order to see that we'd listened he'd start asking us questions about the stories afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember a funeral in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well the first funeral I remember was my eldest sister. She was eighty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You don't remember a funeral before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh the only one was burying the baby when it was five days old. But I've no memory of that, I expect my father and my elder brother went.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You don't remember particular mourning clothes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No, it was my - eighty-two year old sister that was the first - no, it was my brother, sixty-eight and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your parents take you out to visit friends or neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, sometimes I'd go with my father and mother. When I was seven I got dip}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 htheria and r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 heumatic fever and they took me round }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 to Llan Drillog and Canwyd and L}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 lan Elyr wh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 ee I had an aunt. And they took}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
 me to the cathedral there and - I mean after I'd been visiting there for about ten minutes I wanted to go and they were very cross about this and I - you know - when I realized they weren't going to take me away I - I r
ealized that the only thing to do was to start screaming and my father got up and took me out. But my father didn't like it that he was losing - that he was missing the service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go out shopping with your mother or father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, the only time we offered to go shopping was on January the first when we went to Calenig and we offered to go and do the shop}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 ping the, in order that we got Cale}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 nig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Could you tell me a bit about doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well you see - the thing was we weren't allowed 
to go gathering money like this. My mother wouldn't let us. But if we went to - went shopping in the afternoon we weren't allowed out in the morning - in fact they used to give us some money without us asking for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did a lot of children go round gathering money in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 They went - from door to door did they wishing everybody a happy New Year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you remember any more similar customs that children took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. We used to go to the house of Mr. R.O. 
Jones and what he did was to put ha'pennies in the oven to heat them up and he'd throw a whole sau}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
epanful into the gaden and the children would jump over and try and gather them up, and we - and we'd burn our fingers and everyone'd try and gather as many as they could without burning their fingers too much. It was a dirty }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 rick really. But still it was money for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you ever go out with your father alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, only when we went to chapel. I used to walk with him a lot more after I went to the bank. When I was on my holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember any outings you went on with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - I remember - occasionally going to the farms in Llan Rywst or St Asaph and what happened was me and my younger brother used to leave my parents with the family and we'd go out stealing gooseberries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you ever go on holiday anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well we'd go to Pwllheli usually. And sometimes to Crythec.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh - two weeks.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, yes, once a year and we'd leave my older brothers and sisters to look after the shop. Any my mother and father and the younger children would go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of things did you do on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh - usually we just went in the sea. And sometimes we'd go on holiday to my uncle's place at Cae Newydd, the other side of Maentwrog.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well mainly we kicked a football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 In the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, and some - sometimes we'd go to a f
ield in Maenod and we'd play matches with different teams, or we'd play on the back road behind the house, that's where we played most football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well Sunday - it was chapel at ten o'clock, then we'd go to the one o'clock meeti
ng and then Sunday school at two, the five o'clock meeting to learn to sing and then to the sixo'clock service. Then we'd go to the prayer meeting on Monday and then - on - Tuesdays and Wednesday we'd go to a meeting connecting with the Sayat because the 
big - the main Sayat was on - every month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of thing was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well you see every Leader in the chapel had his lists and - and so many people were allocated to each Leader and it was an opportunity for people to talk together, better tha
n they would in a larger meeting. That was the idea. In fact it was John Wesley's idea. Yes, they were class meetings. That was the English people called them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did you do, did you talk about relig}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 on and the chapel and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, well you
 were given an opportunity to take part which you wouldn't have done otherwise if you'd been in a big crowd. That was John Wesley's idea. But that's gone now. It's gone by the board a long time now. And then there was a community meeting on Thursday and t
he Band of Hope on Friday. And every Saturday night in the Vestry of Jerusalem, the different Band of Hopes would take it in turn to entertain for an evening. And the vestry was completely packed out. It was a very big vestry in Jerusalem.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was this Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No. Jerusalem was independent. It just so happened that it had the biggest vestry, and each chapel took its turn to entertain there. And each chapel would take it over for the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you wear different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, we did. And as soon as we got back from chapel we had to take off our jacket and waistcoat and put on our everyday clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh no. I was given a slap by my father for whistling on Sunday. He was very strict on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about working and playing on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, I mean I couldn't even go for a walk, on a hot day in summer we were allowed to go and stand - the back garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You said your parents went to chapel, which denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well the Wesleyans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How often did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh they went regularly. My mother went in the morning, my mother was a Baptist in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she continue to go to the Baptist chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 She changed when she got married did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Yes, yes, she came - then she went with my father. But on one of us were christened until we were older, just before we were accepted as members of chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was this in order that you could choose which religion you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, we did t
his when we were between thirteen and fourteen. And we could choose whether we wanted to be completely immersed in water or just have a spoonful, but most of us were chr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 stened - you know, we weren't immersed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go on Sunday school trips?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, regularly. And those went to Rwllheli as a rule. And once we went to Barmouth and once we went to Rhyl. We got up at four o'clock to catch the five o'clock train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You've talked a bit about the activities you took part in with the chapel but did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No, I was never a member of any choir. Only the odd one for - for sport really when I was enrolled, you know, there might have been a - a small eistedford or something. I just did it to fill in the gap as it were, but my b
rothers, I mean, they were with the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You said you went to the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Oh yes, I went to the Band of Hope regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of things did you do with the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well the bulk of it was learning to sing. To sing and recite. And if possible we learnt not to be naughty children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Can you remember belonging to any other club what had been organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No - no other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You said your father said grace be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 ore meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, every time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And your father did it did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, except that sometimes he asked us to - especially if a preacher had come round to see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they teach you to say prayers before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, all the time. And when we were small children we had to say it in front of them before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You mentioned that you had family prayers or a family service on a Sunday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, we got it every Sunday night. Yes, my father read and I mean if there were friends of my brothe
rs and sisters around we had singing. Learn new songs, new melodies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your father take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. But I mean he had a one track mind, he was Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 But he never took any part in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 He was Lloyd George's man and nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you know why he felt like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean that's what the bulk of people were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about your mother, did she take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was she Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, as far as I know. I mean sh
e'd vote like my father. That's what they all did in the old days, most of them anyway. I mean, families as a rule voted the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember your father or mother in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, I can't remember. But you know I 
mean as children, I mean when we were children we weren't interested in things like that. It didn't matter to us who went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 In so}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
e areas at that time people felt that they risked losing their jobs or their houses if they voted in a different way to their employer, do you have any recollection of this happening to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well no, I mean it was his business. He had his own business so nothing like that came into it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 There was no pressure from the landlord or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no. No
, I mean that sort of thing happened long before that. I mean maybe he felt - it happened when he was a little boy and I'm sure he remembered things like that you know when the landlord said that unless you voted like me you get the sack. But you have to 
go very far back to find that happening. To remember those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember if your mother or father were a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, they weren't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember them working for any of the parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. None of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Not even at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - Thursday afternoon was the only time they didn't work, then they'd go somewhere for the afternoon, probably for a walk somewhere.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember your mother having any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Very few, I mean, she'd go and visit the odd friend from time to time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she go out to enjoy herself to any sort of social occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well I mean there wasn't anyt
hing like that in Blaenau in those days. I mean she only went to chapel. Everything was in its place in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When did your father finish work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well about five to six as a rule. But if something wanted - somebody wanted some thing special he'd carry on later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he spend his evenings at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, he did as a rule, unless he went to - to any of the chapel functions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember your father going to any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I mean he always refused to go into pubs. Now even with me and he always said, you know, that - he's not going to start now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother drink at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No. Even though a her sister kept a pub in - in Cynwyd. No, they were strict T.T's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your father take part in sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, not as far as a I can remember. I mean he'd play cards and things in the house but not games outside the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he go to horse racing or put best on horses or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother or father belong to a savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh no, there was no - no mention of a savings club or anything like that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about putting money a side for funerals or when you were sick or towards shoes? Was there anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I haven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 t any recollection of that. Nothing formal like that. No, I haven't any memory of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean we used to get on quite well without quarrelling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - my younger brother was the one that was nearest to my age and it was with him that I used to go everywhere to play. The others were a step above because they were - there were thirteen years between my eldest brother and me and el
even between me and my other brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When you were a boy who did you play with, your brothers and sisters or someone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well I played with my younger brother and boys about the same age as me, in - in the neighbourhood, yes, we'd play on 
the back road except when we went swimming. We'd walk up to Mango Lake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go to your friends houses to play at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, not to - not to play but to stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh kicking around a ball. That's what we usually did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, we'd be covered in mud when we went home and our trousers be full of holes, and your shirt would be hanging out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were you free to play with whoever you chose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes. No, there was no distinction made between anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you belong to any youth organisations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well I was with a drama company, with the chapel when I was in Corwyna. I was the secretary in fact, but then the producer gave up and I took his place
, when the producer wasn't there I took his place, and I used to help a bit with the the Eslsh League of Youth, just before they went to an Eistedford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you spend your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I just went to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have any pets at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I didn't. My older brother did - my eldest brother. But - you know, the dog had to do for the whole family in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about collecting things like stamps or cigarette cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes,
 I used to gather cigarette cards. I collected a lot of those and I used to stick them all on a big board and put them up in the workshop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You didn't do any gardening, did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well my eldest brother fished and I went with him a couple of times but I didn't fish myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, we used to walk a lot. We used to go down to Maentwrog and places and once about six or seven of us started off to Horlwyn and one of the boys suggested we should eat our sandwic
hes to save carrying them up to the top and after we'd eaten our sandwiches one of them suggested that - well there was on point in going to the top now. And we all went home. And I mean - that's as far as I've ever got up the Moerwyn, I've been up Mannod
 quite a few times, both the Mannogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well - I got my first bike after I'd gone to the bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you do all these things with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well in my life I've taken part in practically everything except rugby. Used to play tennis, badminton, golf, cricket, football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about going to the theatre or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh when I was in the bank in Moul I used to go to Chester and Liverpool to go to the theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about concerts and music hall when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well there was a concert in Blaenau nearly every week. It was a sort of charity concert to help somebody who was ill. And they were pretty good concerts too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you remember going to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, we used to go to the pictures in the old days, - it was a penny to go in. Silent movies. And then it went up to tuppence. It was up in the Central Hall but before that it was the Salvation Army place, and we'd go to the pe
nny pictures on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well we'd get a ha'penny unless we wanted to got the pictures. You know we could get a lot of sweets for a ha'penny, to compare with now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And as a rule you did spend it on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Except when we wanted to go to the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You told me that your mother had somebody in to help her with the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well she was a - a woman - friend of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And she only got help with the washing did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Yes. And I mean she very rarely had that, just on special occasions when she washed the sheets or something and I mean with the just regular washing, weekly washing she did it on her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 If your mother was ill and had to stay in bed how did you manage, how did the house get done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh my eldest sisters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember what happened when your younger brother was born, how did your mother manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I - I haven't got much recollection of when he was born. I remember the baby being born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What happened, did she have any outside help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, she didn't. No, there were three girls old enough to do everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your parents have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, I mean my mother's sister lived where the launderette is now. It was an ironmongery shop, Jonathon Edwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How much did you see of these relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh I saw them pretty often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go to their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, and they came to our house too. And my cousin, he was an artist, Cerdd Edwards. But he's died - he died a long time ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember much about your parents friends, did they share similar friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh-they had a lot of friends and they'd call off and on, and then they'd call in their houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Nobody exceptional as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about your father, did he have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. He was friends with everybody sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 So your mother and father shared friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were the friends invited to the house? You said they were, were they offered something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, every time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were there any special occasions or special days when visitors were invited to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. But Thursdays were my mother's freest days because the shop shut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Would you say the friends that came to see you were your mother's friends, your father's friends, or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh friends of both. None of them were sort of special to one or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And the friends came without an invitation didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, I mean they came to the shop mainly. And then very often none of them would go without having a chat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 We're told that people in t
hose days made their own amusements, do you remember your parents getting together with friends and neighbours in order to sing or dance or play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - yes, because we had many a concert in the house. I even remember my sister singing to a record, you know, those old fashioned ones.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they play games together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well there were lots of games but I can't remember which ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 A lot of people divide society up into different classes or groups, would you say that in the time before 
1918 that society was divided up in this way? That people either belonged to one group or another group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean - you know - I'd say that - I mean in Blaunau - Blaenau - was full of ordinary people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 There wasn't a sort of upper curst or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well very little. The ones that houses in their own grounds say. And they weren't that snobbish either. I mean, they'd stop and talk to you in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about the quarry owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - I mean - the quarry manager had a big house and very often they belonged to the councils.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of group would you say you belonged to, what social group? With ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes. I'm just an ordinary man in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You've already said people in Blaenau were much the same as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, I mean Blaenau had ordinary people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of people would you say belonged to other groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 But there were very few so called snobs that have ever been here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember being b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987750\charrsid7017564 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 ought up to respect some people differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, I don't. I was bought up to treat everybody the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember touching your cap or showing respect in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, we had to do that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 To who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh to the te
achers and to a woman and to the preacher. No, no, I don't have any recollection of doing it to the Minister. And sometimes to your bank manager, I mean we had to take our caps off completely before going in to a bank in the old days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember calling anyone sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well you had to say sir to the teachers. Or anyone who was older than you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh - well only the children that were with me, I never heard anyone else do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 In this town who would you say were the important people? What types of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well as I was saying, bank managers, quarry managers, anyone who had a higher status than the ordinary man in the street. Headmasters.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you come into contact with these people much?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, very little because I mean I left home when I was sixteen and I wasn't interested in them before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember why they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - well it's because their status was higher, than most peoples. Their position in society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 With each other more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about the Ministers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh they were the same, they mixed with the chapel people. Quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - I haven't really much recollection of seeing teacher mixing much with people, but I mean they came to chapel and they took quite a good part in the community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well, I v
ery rarely saw farmers in Blaenau, except for the farmer from Owm Bowydd. That was really the only farm except for Gelling Isas. That was just a small farm though. Owm Bowydd was the only sizeable farm in Blaenau that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about the employers, did they mix with people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well I mean - the employers really were only connected with the quarry in those days. Well I mean, they - well I mean most of them, they weren't around anyway. But - there were the managers. And I mean they drank with each othe
r, but not of course with the workers. I mean, they might have done but I never heard of it. I never heard of them mixing with the quarrymen. No, they mixed with people like themselves when they went to the pubs. Even though - I mean I didn't go to pubs i
n those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of people would you say went to church, were they different from the chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well there was the old idea long ago that Tories went to the church, but I mean there's nothing in that. I mean, you know, Gladstone was a
 great Liberal and a High Church man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of people went to the chapel would you say?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well at the time of the Revival all sorts of people went. They came out of the pubs to give themselves up but it didn't last very long for most. That.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was that in 1904?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, 1904.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Would you say that the ordinary people of Blaenau had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes. Yes, on average they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember feeling that some ordinary people felt themselves to be superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No, I don't remember anything like that in Balaenau because - a lot of people in those days read a lot and they realized that they were on the same level. They read a lot. There was nothing else for them to do. There was nothing else that they could do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember any families being described as rough and others as respectable? There weren't any outcasts or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no. I've no memory of that, no body was called a snob}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 or anything. But I mean of course there were lots of very poor people in Blaenau at that time, and usually it was families with lots of children and they didn't have enough money to keep them properly.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You don't remember people who made trouble in the quarry being called rough or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No, the only ones you'd see was - on a Saturday night say, they'd be drunk and I mean beer in those days was beer, which it isn't now, and the police had a lot of trouble on the Saturday. Yes, they had to take them to the police station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember any distinction being made between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No I don't. Unless it was in the quarry itself, but outside that there was no distinction made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitudes to people in different backgrounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I never heard them running anyone down, even people who didn't pay them, and there were a lot of those.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember your mother feeling that she belonged to a particular group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I don't - there was nothing, you kn
ow - when I was a child, nothing like social groups. The only thing was which chapel or which church you went to. That was the most important thing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember anyone in Blaenau moving up into a different class or group, rising from very small beginnings to be something quite big?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, a lot became professors in the university. Cledwyn Owen is one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Why do you think such people were able to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well there was a very good school in Blaenau and a lot of people did very well after they left this school and went to the colleges.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well there was this - this boy who went to the Wesleyan chapel in Mannog, William Jones from Dryn Awel. Everyone
 sort of - you know whenever he was around people would - stop swearing in his hearing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Why was he a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well everyone said he was a man of God, didn't matter where they saw him or who they were. And William Roberts who lived in Maen
twrog, he was the same type. A tramp wouldn't go and beg in Maentwrog, he'd skirt round for reason that this - this man, William Roberts, lived there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was he afraid of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, he was afraid of him. I mean there was nothing in it but he was onl
y a small man but one of the nicest people to talk to but he was a man of God and that was enough to make the tramp steer clear of him. He knew he was doing wrong - begging when he ought to be working, that was the idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes, we had him all the time, we called him Bobby Run. Oh yes, we used to do thing purposely to upset the policeman and get him to chase us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean we just used to tea
se him, it was just fun. We did it for fun. The policeman was never nasty, but I did get frightened once when the sergeant got hold of me, come here, he said, and took me up to the old police station - up by Cw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 n Beryk Road, took me into the old police station there, asked me my name. Wh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 's son are you? That was the only time I really got frightened.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How would you say policemen treated people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well they were pretty rough with people who got drunk on a Saturday night, there's no dou
bt about that. Only - in other respects they were very fair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No, it wasn't. My father bought it on a mortgage. It was ground rent you see. And when ground rent came to an end he bought it on a mortgage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 So you didn't have a landlord then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well it was a struggle long ago when the business was getting started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you feel towards this struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean as children we had plenty to eat and yo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 
u know we didn't know the strugg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
le that they were going through, but you know no doubt I mean ten pounds of butter in a week - I mean if you had to pay for ten pounds of butter now it would be pretty heavy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you know if it made a difference to the family if your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well I don't remember the old man being ill. Not in the old days. He was eighty-eight when he died and I've no recollection of my mother being ill either, until she died that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you ever get charity from the parish at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. Didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 If there was a person in this area who the people objected to very strongly was there any way of showing this disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I've seen very little jealousy in Balenau. Jealousy amongst anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Do you ever remember people being forced to leave the area because other people had made rough music outside their houses? A great noise outside their house to drive them out of the town?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I've no memory of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you don't remember people making }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 ffigies of people they disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember having lessons from your parents or a private tutor at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, I've no recollection of that, only in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 I was four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When you first started when did you go to school? And when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 I went at nine and finished at three o'clock. Not like today, they finish earlier now. The infants that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, it was Haenofferen school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was it just boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, from standard one upwards, but the infants mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 I walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh five to ten minutes at the outside, depending on whether we ran or crawled there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Who did you go to school with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 My brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh, at home. No, there was no - there were no school dinners in the old days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you feel towards the school, did you like or dislike it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - I have no recollection of hating it at all, I went along with the other children, all the same way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you feel towards the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well the odd one I disliked and I let him know it too. I quite often upset him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember the teachers emphasising some things as being important in life, like manners or tidiness, or punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - very little, especially before going to the County School
. The teachers bothered very little with that sort of thing. Please yourself was the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they emphasise ways of speaking at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, not really, the only thing we weren't to do was swear and fight. There was nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 They didn't want you to speak correct Welsh or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 If you did something that the teachers disapproved of what happened, how were you punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh we had a thrashing, and in the County School on our behinds but in the other school it was - on our hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did the girls have the same punishments as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Yes, yes, the girls were caned, but they weren't given a thrashing in the County school. They got detention and - adding up long strings of numbers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 For what sort of things were you punished in school? In the primary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh for talking in the classroom or for making a blot on the copy book. Small things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes. Specially when I was in the county school because they had reports from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they go and visit your primary school teachers at all or go to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, not - not as far as I know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 In the primary school would you say that the children who went there were from the same types of background as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, they were the same type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember the teachers singling out some children for different treatment from others, favouritism or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, I didn't see anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were there gangs in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes, there was a crowd together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of things did these crowds do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh they'd fight and beat each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were there some children who were left out of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well there were some
 that were too shy to join in and of course - I mean, I didn't bother with those and if there was some person who was particularly rough we'd make sure we got hold of him when we were in a gang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How old were you when you went to the county school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well - I left in 1912 when I was sixteen, I must have been about twelve, eleven to twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you went by nine o'clock and came home at half past three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. We did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 This was a mixed school wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Yes, every class was mixed in the County school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you walked to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And its the same distance as to the primary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Who did you go with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh with the boys who lived around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have school dinners at the County?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you feel towards this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I thought that - the big people, the important people went to the County school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you do an eleven plus or anything to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I did the Central Welsh Board Junior. There w
as a Junior and Senior in those days and I passed the Junior exam the year I tried it and I was offered a job in the bank and I went. But if I'd have gone on I'd have tried the Senior exam the next year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you do an exam in the primary school in order to get the opportunity to go to the county?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, I did. I passed the Oakley scholarship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You mean given by the Oakley quarry people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, there was three places given every year. With the Oakley scholarship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you feel towards the teachers in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well quite good except for one, old Edmunds, but he went to Pat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 a}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 gonia afterwards. You know, he told on me when he saw me - escaping out of school one day. I was climbing over the wall because I didn't have anything for 
the last two lessons on a Friday so I tried to slip out at playtime over the wall and go down through the woods to home but old Edmunds saw me out of a top window, and he saw me running down and he told the headmaster and the next day I had to go and see 
the headmaster in the house there and he asked me way I was escaping. I told - then I told him that I saw no purpose in studying in the school, I could see nature outside. I got a thrashing in the end. Twenty-one strokes - and he was able to thrash too.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember the teachers emphasising certain things in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - it was the lessons - it was the lessons that were most important to them. They told us that we'd got to pick up what they were teaching. And it was bob's your uncle if you don't pick it up now it's your own fault.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Were the girls caned at the county school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No, I've no idea how the girls were punished. I got a thrashing, that's all. And probably too often. Unless the girls just had detention on the Friday after - Friday evening and the long strings of numbers to add up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Apart from escaping out of school what other things were you punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well one time I started pulling up the - the small trees round the side in order to hit another boy. I think 
that was the worst sin I committed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did your parents take an interest in your county schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes, they - and I had to do my homework too, first thing after tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they go to see the teachers and the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I've not much recollection of a speech day. No, no. That's a more recent thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Would you say that the county school children were from the same backgrounds and homes as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, a lot of them were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember the teachers singing out some children for different treatment in the county?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I never saw a teacher fussing anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember gangs or groups in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, I mean the same as everywhere else. I mean if you'd sinned against one group or one crowd you h
ad to look out they didn't catch you on your way home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about children being left out of things, were any left out here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 I can't say I noticed. Some people were upset 'cos they weren't in the football team. But then you - I mean you couldn't
 have more than eleven in the team.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When did you leave school, when you were sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Would you have stayed on if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I was offered a chance in a bank so I took it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you take any part time education, evening classes or anything like that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No, I didn't. 'Cos you see when I was in the bank I did exams there. But they didn't emphasise them so much when I first went to the bank. They didn't emphasise the exams. 
For - until about fifteen years later really, then they started emphasizing them and I mean it had gone too late for me to start studying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you have any regrets about your education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you think it did you good, you benefited from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 When you were at school did you have a part time job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I didn't get any money from anywhere. I might ask my father for a job and try carving or something because he carved the chairs for th
e }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
istedford, the Bardic chair and sometimes I'd ask him for a job to carve a little small thing in order to learn to carve. And that's the only recollection I have of doing anything - in connection with carpentry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How many hours would you do this with your father in a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh - Saturday afternoon maybe. Only it had to be a went a Saturday afternoon otherwise I wouldn't be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you remember exactly what your father did in his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh he made cupboards and things, and he made Bardic chairs for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 E}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 istedford. He made the big chair for the Corwyn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16191275\charrsid7017564 E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
istedford, and I mean the legs and the arms had all been carved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 But he didn't pay you for working in the shop did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. No he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you feel this fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well 
I mean in that - in those days they didn't have any money to throw away. I mean if I had a penny from someone I thought I'd had a fortune - that's how money was in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You didn't do anything else apart from working with your father, did you get along well with your father as a man to work with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh to me it was just something to pass the time, it wasn't really work. I mean he didn't really want help. All I wanted to do was to learn to carve for myself, for my own benefit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you think beginning to do these things with your father changed your attitude to school at all, did it make you want to leave school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, I never wanted to leave school, until I got the chance of going to the bank that is. And I did the exam and I mean a
ll the detentions I've had adding up all those numbers came in useful for this exam because I'd - I had to add up long lists of numbers and in order to go to the bank - to be accepted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What exactly did you have to do in the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I was the - the small clerk. The little clerk. First thing I had to do was address envelopes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You started at the bank in 1912?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How many hours did you work in the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh we started at nine and the doors opened at ten. They were shut at th
ree, and it depended - some days we were out by four and other times about six, depended how busy it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about Sundays, you didn't work Sundays, did you work Saturdays at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Saturday morning though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you ever get holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh yes. We got two weeks in the first ten years, three weeks up to twenty years and a month after that. You haven't asked me how much I earned in the beginning have you? Well I got twenty pounds a year and I was living - I was living away in 
Darmouth. I got one pound thirteen and four a month and I paid eight shillings a month for - n, eight shillings a week for rooms. That was one pound twelve, and I only had one and four spare, but I got some help from my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you feel that this pay was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well I think the idea was that a young boy should learn the value of money. Because if he had too much money he might start squandering it in the beginning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you think it's right to feel this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean obviously we com
plained but we didn't have enough to spend and of course I was lucky, I mean a glass of - a half a pint of bitter was a penny in those days. I mean it's one and six now isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you give any of the money you earned to your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I mean I had to have help from them for about five or six years. And anyway after that they didn't want anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh I pulled together with everyone. I treated the top dog and the bottom dog at the same level - as if they were at the same level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did your employer or manager treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Oh I managed O.K. with all of them. But I did quarrel with the accountant sometimes. But I knew that the manager was more friendly with me than he was with the accountant so it was all right. I knew I could fight with the accountant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you feel towards the work itself, did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, I liked the work from the beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did starting work change your attitude to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I forgot about school just like that. I just didn't think about it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you stayed with the bank all your life after that didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes. Yes, for forty-four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 How did you climb the ladder within the banking world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - first of all I was a cashier after the first world war, from when I moved to Moul from Denbigh I became a cashier, and then I became an accountant when I moved from Denbigh to Borwyan and then Corwyn I became clerk in charge when I
 went to Trawsfynydd and then I was a manager in Llan Ffestiniog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Would you have preferred another job, to do something else with your life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I never thought of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you ever serve an apprenticeship or do some form of training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No I didn't, I refused to join. But in fact the National Union of Bank Employees only came very recently and I was a manager before they came so of course I wasn't interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Do you think that employers and workers and the same attitude to life, their interest in life, did they see the world in the same way?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well in the bank I felt - I felt that the top dog and bottom dog pulled together O.K. There was nothing snobbish about the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about in the wider community, would you say there was a division between workers and employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no. Well not in the bank anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about outside the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well I mean I didn't really notice much outside the bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And there weren't any divisions between the workers in the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well there were because some people didn't try to get ahead, they didn't want to, they didn't want promotion or anything, they'd say that they were quite satisfied to go year by 
year doing the same thing. Yes. Well - and they'd get a pay rise up to a certain point, then after that you have to fight for it and then it was their fault if they didn't get a rise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You said you felt there was no distinction between craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well that's how I felt anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Would you say that working full time changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, it didn't. It was something that came naturally to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 After you left school you didn't live at home at all did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No I didn't, except when I came home for a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did starting work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No it didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Nor with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. It stayed the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I - still went to chapel. Maybe not quite so often as when I was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And you still went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, I became a Sunday school teacher, with the older girls in Trawsfynydd and before that on Corwyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I didn't. Only to try and upset someone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you ever feel pressurized to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No I didn't. No, I voted for each one of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Have you ever been a member of a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Have you ever worked for one at the time of an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you still send your free time in the same way as you had when you'd been at home or did you change your leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I mean, I played mostly. I enjoyed life. That seems to be a bit stupid to other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go out in the evenings more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes, I was out every evening?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did you go and with who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well if it was the summer I might go and play tennis or golf. Or hockey or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You'd go with your friends would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you make a lot of new friends, girls or boys, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, yes, I've got a lot of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did you meet these friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well mainly in the tennis club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you take them home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, I mean I was in lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 But you never bought them up to Blaenau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh no, no, no, I never bought anyone up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, everyone was friends with me. I never made a fuss of any particular one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Where did you go with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - sometimes we'd go to the theatre in Chester, 'cos it was only about ten miles away from Moult. And we'd hire a car and maybe we'd go to Liverpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you go and drink and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh yes, we'd have the odd one on the way home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 You said your family didn't meet these friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I never bothered to bring them home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 And your parents didn't expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, I mean they got a letter from \lquote em every week and that was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about your oldest child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh she went in for Institutional Management. It was a job with a Catholic chur
ch school, but she found out that she'd get more money as a clerk in an office than she'd get in this job and - and I'd paid all her college fees too. So she left and went to become a clerk and she got four pounds a week more for doing this than she got w
hen - you know - after all that studying - and everything. And then - then she married and she lives in Llanon, the other side of Aberystwyth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What was her husband's work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well he was on the railway when they met and then he got a job with the fruit people. I can't remember who they were though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What sort of thing did they do? Did they distribute fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, they canned fruit. And then he saw an advert that said they wanted a technician in Aberystwyth University in the physics labora
tory. And he got that job and now he's a chief technician.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did he do on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh, he wasn't there very long but he worked with the - with repairs I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about your other child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh he went to the Civil Service in Lon
don and he went up to Liverpool, but he got tired of Liverpool and went back to London. He was with the Ministry of Aviation first. And when the Welsh office came into being he applied for entrance and got accepted in the Welsh office. And then he'd been 
i
n the Welsh office for about a month and the results of the exam he'd tried came out and he heard that he'd been made an executive officer and since the officers had just been appointed to the Welsh office there was no room for an executive officer there,
 
so he had to take another section of the Civil Service. The first one that had an opening, and he went to - Wadnsworth with the Social Security and he's been there for about seven years. And he's just gone to Cardiff last November to do staff training for
 the Ministry of Social Security. And he's in his element teaching people - young people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about your brothers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well my eldest brother was a carpenter. He worked with my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he take your father's business over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, he got 
ill in the first world war, he got colitis and he was in bed for ten or twelve years. And - well I mean he was a - a carpenter but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did he work after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No, no, he didn't work although he lived 'til he was eighty-seven, he was an invalid. Bu
t he was with the first Maerwyn choir that went to America.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What about the other brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well the brother next to him, he's eighty-six on Saturday. Well he was a - a Minister in the - with the English Wesleyans. And then he went out to India a
s a Wesleyan. And - I suppose you know he mixed with the Army quite a lot and met people from the Church of England and - when they came back his wife wanted him to; change to the Church of England because they were more snobby than the Wesleyan chapel an
d
 he did join to. And my father said to me, there's a man who's fallen out of the race as it were. And - he was with the Anglicans after that and he only retired about three years ago. Well he's in Gloucestershire, he used to walk four miles every morning 
to keep fit and my younger brother died when he was sixty-eight and a half. He kept a furniture shop and a cabinet makers business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 That's what he did all his life was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes, yes, that's right. No, wait a minute, before the second world war he 
went to Scunthorpe to work in the steelworks as a metallurgical chemist and then at the end of the war the steelworks didn't want half the people and he got the - and the youngest people got the sack there and he came back and took over my father's busine
ss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 That's all four of the brothers, then there were four sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Well the oldest sister was a district nurse. No, not a district nurse, a nurse for babies, a midwife. That was in Ruthin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did she get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
No she didn't. But she was courting but her lover died and she died when she was eighty-two, my other sister, she lived in Cardiff. She went there as a servant girl and she married a man from Llan Beris who works in a Labour Exchange. And the old 
boy died a year before he retired from thrombosis and she came to live here in Blaenau about three years ago. And after that she died when she was eighty-two.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Exactly what did she do as a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh well she looked after childre
n for a German family. And she picked quite a lot of German up then. But she was a dressmaker first of all with an aunt of mine. And my two other sisters were both teachers. One's eighty-one and the other's seventy-nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Did they go to college first and then become teachers? What about the husbands' of the ones that married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 
Well - Hannah, the one's that in the square now, she married a school attendance officer for this county. But I mean, he's died six years now. And the other one's a - a - spi
nster. She's the one that's eighty-one. She was a teacher at the slate quarries. And she also worked in Wrexham and Trawsfynydd. And the other one, the one that's in Park Square, she worked in Tintan, do you know where that is? You know, up by Trawfynydd 
- at the entrance where you go through to the camp - Army Camp. Bronaber is the real name. And then she came to Blaenau after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Two of your sisters got married then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 What did your wife do before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Oh she was a clerk with an auctioneer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927121 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 Was she worked at all after marrying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14549322 HD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9993697\charrsid7017564 No. She's only looked after me, and that's enough work.
\par }}